<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1035,1338,1365]" box="[151,1035,1338,1365]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,1035,1338,1365]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1035,1338,1365]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
Is 
<taxonomicName authority="Dognin, 1906" authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1906" box="[181,614,1338,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praphoea">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,441,1338,1365]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Robinsonia praphoea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dognin, P." box="[449,614,1338,1364]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" pagination="178 - 186" refId="ref7815" refString="Dognin, P. (1906) Heteroceres nouveaux de l'Amerique du Sud. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 50, 178 - 186. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10597" type="journal article" year="1906">Dognin, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
really present in 
<collectingCountry box="[831,1023,1338,1365]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
?
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1411,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laguerre" authorityYear="2021" box="[274,402,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,402,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Robinsonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is commonly present in 
<collectingCountry box="[677,842,1411,1437]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
with at least ten species. One of the most common is traditionally identified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Dognin, 1906" authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1906" box="[442,851,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praphoea">
<emphasis box="[442,685,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Robinsonia praphoea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dognin, P." box="[693,851,1447,1473]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" pagination="178 - 186" refId="ref7815" refString="Dognin, P. (1906) Heteroceres nouveaux de l'Amerique du Sud. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 50, 178 - 186. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10597" type="journal article" year="1906">Dognin, 1906</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This species was described on a single male specimen collected on Rio Inambari, La Oroya, Carabaya in the 
<collectingRegion box="[813,871,1483,1509]" country="Peru" name="Puno" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Puno</collectingRegion>
department (
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1075,1483,1509]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Peru</collectingCountry>
), the 
<typeStatus box="[1135,1183,1483,1509]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">type</typeStatus>
is housed in Washington (see 
<figureCitation box="[249,313,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,563,587]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,537]" captionTargetId="figure-25@2.[151,1436,179,537]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Robinsonia praphoea Dognin, 1906. A: male holotype. B: fresh sequenced specimen from Peru (Cuzco), photo courtesy of G. Brehm (PMJ)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982835" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982835/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) and has been dissected by A. Watson in 1971 (see plate 120 a, b in 
<bibRefCitation author="Watson, A." box="[1101,1258,1519,1545]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" pagination="1 - 361" refId="ref9014" refString="Watson, A. (1971) An Illustrated Catalog of the Neotropic Arctiinae Types in the United States National Museum (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae), Part I. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, Washington, N ° 50, 1 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.50" type="journal article" year="1971">Watson, 1971</bibRefCitation>
, slide reference AW2 and a fresh dissection below in 
<figureCitation box="[580,650,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1128,1152]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,648,1105]" captionTargetId="figure-50@2.[151,1436,648,1105]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. A–E: male genitalia of Robinsonia praphoea Dognin, 1906, reference ML3291. A ventral view, B dorsal view, C lateral view, D valva view from inside, E aedeagus with everted vesica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982837/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). During a routine survey of the 
<collectingCountry box="[1027,1194,1555,1581]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
Arctiinae, 
<specimenCount box="[1320,1436,1555,1581]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" type="male">two males</specimenCount>
collected in the coastal area (Kaw Road) were dissected and we were very surprised to find genitalia completely different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1906" box="[320,461,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praphoea">
<emphasis box="[320,461,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">R. praphoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
despite very similar habitus. Moreover within BOLD it was possible to find one sequence of a specimen similar to the 
<typeStatus box="[558,606,1663,1689]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1906" box="[645,783,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praphoea">
<emphasis box="[645,783,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">R. praphoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and collected by G. Brehm around 
<quantity box="[1187,1272,1663,1689]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
to the West of the 
<typeStatus box="[193,241,1699,1725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">type</typeStatus>
locality and at the same altitude (see 
<figureCitation box="[666,731,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,563,587]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,179,537]" captionTargetId="figure-25@2.[151,1436,179,537]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Robinsonia praphoea Dognin, 1906. A: male holotype. B: fresh sequenced specimen from Peru (Cuzco), photo courtesy of G. Brehm (PMJ)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982835" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982835/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). This sequence differs by at least 7.8 % from three sequences obtained from 
<collectingCountry box="[313,478,1735,1761]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
specimens (see 
<figureCitation box="[656,723,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1655,1679]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,1218,1628]" captionTargetId="figure-88@2.[151,1436,1213,1631]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neighbour-Joining tree of 17 selected COX1 sequences of the studied group, distances in % are given below each branch and bootstrap supports are given above each branch in bold (only if larger than 70 %) (obtained with MEGA7, see Ku- maR et al., 2016). The newly described species are highlighted in bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4982839" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4982839/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). It then appears that the 
<taxonomicName box="[998,1212,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[998,1126,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Robinsonia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
commonly found in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,316,1771,1797]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
is not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dognin" authorityYear="1906" box="[390,528,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="praphoea">
<emphasis box="[390,528,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">R. praphoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but a new species which is described below under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Laguerre" authorityName="Laguerrre" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Robinsonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1203,1437,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">Robinsonia simulans</emphasis>
Laguerre
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[266,356,1807,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[266,356,1807,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="66" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
